The paper presents a code package for numerically integrating the nonlinear Schrodinger equation using high-order finite-difference schemes and GPU parallel architectures. This falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). The package also interfaces with MATLAB, which falls under the category of mathematical software (cs.MS). The use of GPU parallel architectures also suggests the possibility of scientific computing (cs.SC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
